(167, 72, 'KE May-18 Bill / Invoice', '^info@burhanisolutions.com.pk', '^noreply@billingke.com.pk', '', NULL, '\nDear Customer, Your K-Electric bill for May-18 is attached. We are pleased to announce that K-Electric has redesigned its bill for all customers. This has been done to better facilitate you, our consumer, in reading and understanding your bill. The graphic attached outlines the key features of the new bill. Further details are available on the KE website, including the new bill layout and FAQs. Please download and print this attachment to pay your bill as per your convenience. Now you do not have to wait for the physically distributed bill to arrive. You may also retrieve your Duplicate Bill through our official website. KE has already made arrangements with all banks to receive your electricity bill’s printed copy. You can pay your bill at all your bank’s counter, or bill collection service outlets across Karachi and Hub, or you can visit our IBC Bank Booths of Telenor Micro Finance Bank at F.B. Area, Garden, Liaquatabad, North Karachi, Baldia, Orangi-II, Lyari (West Wharf). In case you do not want to print this bill, our alternate payment facility offers various electronic modes of bill payment for your convenience. You may present your 13-digit KE account number at any Easy Paisa Shop, UBL Omni Dukaan, HBL Express retailer, NADRA e-Sahulat franchise, Jazzcash retailer, UPaisa outlet or visit a 1Link ATM of your own bank. For online payment, log in to your Internet Banking portal or Mobile Banking App and select the KE bill payment option or use your Credit/Debit Card of HBL, Bank Alfalah, Allied Bank, Faysal Bank, MCB, UBL, Silk Bank and Standard Chartered Bank. Upon using any of the above alternate payment modes you will receive either a slip, email or SMS from the respective Payment Channel which will serve as the receipt of your payment. KE is committed to providing maximum convenience and best in class service to its customers. Please visit www.ke.